  title: Dining Room
  description: The dining room was one of the most important social spaces in a wealthy
    household. Formal meals were often served in multiple courses and followed strict
    etiquette rules, with servants preparing and presenting food while guests gathered
    to dine, socialize, and discuss business or politics.
